 President Muhammadu Buhari will, Thursday, embark on a two-day visit to Kaduna State. It was learnt that among other places, the president would visit Kafanchan in Southern Kaduna and other major towns in the state to inaugurate some projects. The visit to Kaduna State would end on Friday, a statement from Sir Kashim Ibrahim House stated. The statement read in parts that ”The president, who will visit the three major towns of Kaduna, Zaria and Kafanchan, will also be shown round road projects across the state, which were executed by the Governor Nasir El Rufai administration.” The statement by the Special Adviser on Media and Communication to Governor El-Rufai, Muyiwa Adekeye, listed the projects to be inaugurated to include the remodeled Murtala Muhammed Square, located at the heart of Kaduna town. It also listed the Infectious Disease Hospital at Mando, the Dangote Peugeot Automobile Nigeria Limited along Kaduna-Abuja Expressway, and the Sabon Gari market in Zaria among the projects to be commissioned. It stated further that the president would also inaugurated projects such as the reconstructed Kawo flyover having three grand rotaries and access roads, as well as the WAFF Road which was dualized with junction improvement. Also, the president would commission road projects in Kafanchan and Zaria. 